An expensive lure.  Those fish wont even know what got them.  The best lure gold can buy.  This lure is hand carved, painted, and is perfectly balenced able to easily fool almost any fish.  It would be a shame to loose it though.

This is an oil flask.  You may use it to refill a lantern, or try to light it and throw at someone
This is a standard cheap disposable torch.
A fly, general used for fishing.  Its more effective than live bait and can be reused as many times as you like, just dont get it caught in the weeds.
Live bate generaly used for fishing.  Its slightly more effective than just a hook but its usualy used quickly.
This is a flute.  It is by no means low-quality, but it is nothing special, either.
Used as often in the peasant's home as the dungeon's dark, these simple concoctions are common throughout Faerun.
These curative potions are too expensive for most civilians, and are used almost exclusively by soldiers and adventurers.
